    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I looked into this a little bit and by removing [these checks](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/6cacdde5630c593999059833b516e1fec60aaf72/pandas/core/reshape/merge.py#L1277-L1288), I was able to merge on multiple keys and it seems to work, also with `direction` and `tolerance` arguments. [Here](https://gist.github.com/MareinK/f3dc5aaa52d01ce2c30e0742361392c8)'s my monkey patch code. However I'm not sure whether the results are correct/as you would expect. I think it may just use the last key in the list. I think that may be changed [here](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/6cacdde5630c593999059833b516e1fec60aaf72/pandas/core/reshape/merge.py#L1386-L1389) but that results in an 'truth value of array is ambiguous' error down the line."
